"'''Imperial Spin'''" is a short story written by [[Greg Gorden]]. The story consists of three holomessages by Imperial advisor [[Ars Dangor/Legends|Ars Dangor]]. It was first printed in the ''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]'' and was later archived on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
In two holomessages, one to the Imperial citizenry and another to the [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moffs]], Ars Dangor announced the abolition of the [[Imperial Senate/Legends|Imperial Senate]] and the transition of administrative authority to the Grand Moffs.

In a holomessage to the military hierarchy and Grand Moffs, Dangor reaffirmed the Empire's commitment to the [[Tarkin Doctrine/Legends|Tarkin Doctrine]] after the Battle of Yavin and announced the creation of [[Death Squadron/Legends|Death Squadron]], led by [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and his flagship, the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|Super Star Destroyer]] [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']].

